enum gaia::core::PackageManagerPriv::PACKAGE_INSTALL_FLAG

Package install flags.

Enumerator:
INSTALL_FORWARD_LOCK 

installPackage indicate that this package should be installed as forward locked.

INSTALL_REPLACE_EXISTING 

installPackage indicate that you want to replace an already installed package.

INSTALL_ALLOW_TEST 

installPackage indicate that you want to allow test packages to be installed.

INSTALL_EXTERNAL 

installPackage indicate that this package has to be installed on the sdcard.

installPackage indicate that this package has to be installed on the sdcard.

const PackageDeleteObserver &  observer,
int32_t  flags 
)

Delete a package.

Since this may take a little while, the result will be posted back to the given observer.

Parameters:
packageNameThe name of the package to delete.
observerAn observer callback to get notified when the package deletion is complete.
flags- possible values: DONT_DELETE_DATA
int32_t gaia::core::PackageManagerPriv::getUidForSharedUser ( const base::String &  sharedUserName) const

Return the user id associated with a shared user name.

Multiple applications can specify a shared user name in their manifest and thus end up using a common uid. This might be used for new applications that use an existing shared user name and need to know the uid of the shared user.

Parameters:
sharedUserNameThe shared user name whose uid is to be retrieved.
Returns:
Returns the uid associated with the shared user.
void gaia::core::PackageManagerPriv::installPackage ( const net::Uri &  uri,
const PackageInstallObserver &  observer,
int32_t  flags,
const base::String &  installerPackageName 
)

Install a package.

Since this may take a little while, the result will be posted back to the given observer.

Parameters:
uriThe location of the package file to install. This can be a 'file:' or a 'content:' URI.
observerAn observer callback to get notified when the package installation is complete.
flags- possible values: INSTALL_FORWARD_LOCK, INSTALL_REPLACE_EXISTING INSTALL_ALLOW_TEST.
installerPackageNameOptional package name of the application that is performing the installation. This identifies which market the package came from.
void gaia::core::PackageManagerPriv::movePackage ( const base::String &  packageName,
const PackageMoveObserver &  observer,
int32_t  flags 
)

Attempts to move package resources from internal to external media or vice versa.

This call may fail if the calling context lacks the android.permission.MOVE_PACKAGE permission, if the named package cannot be found, or if the named package is a "system package".

Parameters:
packageNameThe name of the package to move
observerAn observer callback to get notified when movePackage is completed.
flagsTo indicate install location MOVE_INTERNAL or MOVE_EXTERNAL_MEDIA
